    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Correct the issue is here: https://github.com/ethereum/remix-project/blob/fa7271286ee68e87817237abe986335dc31ff217/libs/remixd/src/services/hardhatClient.ts#L32 \r\nIt tries to watch a folder that does not exist, causing an exception on node 14, but on v16 it just silently fails because of \r\n```\r\nUnhandled promise rejections are deprecated. In the future, promise rejections that are not handled will terminate the Node.js process with a non-zero exit code.\r\n```\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/remix-project/blob/fa7271286ee68e87817237abe986335dc31ff217/libs/remixd/src/services/hardhatClient.ts#L119\r\n\r\nwithout this folder remixd crashes, next release will fix it, meanwhile creating artifacts/contracts before starting remixd will solve it. ",
